Key Match Events: Trent Alexander-Arnold scored a stunning free-kick from the left side of the box to make it 2-0 for England.
Jack Grealish opened the scoring for England with a cool finish after a lovely flick from Angel Gomes.
Declan Rice scored the third goal for England from a cross by substitute Ollie Watkins.
Arttu Hoskonen scored a late consolation goal for Finland, heading home from a corner.
Pre-Game Insights: Lee Carsley needed a win to stabilize his position after the defeat against Greece and the uncertainty around his longer-term role within the England setup.
The match was expected to be more conventional in style, especially with Harry Kane back from injury to play as the No 9.
Post-Match Reflections: Lee Carsley is likely to return to his old job with the under-21s at the end of his interim tenure in November.
The match was seen as a return to the tranquil progress of Carsley's first camp in September.
